&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Research Governance &amp; Quality Manager&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 7; full time 37½ hours/week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;University Hospitals Coventry and Warwickshire NHS Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an individual with strong expertise in research governance and sponsorship to apply for the position of Research Governance &amp; Quality Manager at University Hospitals Coventry &amp; Warwickshire (UHCW) NHS Trust. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Post:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Research Governance &amp; Quality Manager is an integral role in leading and managing teams that facilitate and support clinical trials and research governance. They will be responsible for supporting and enabling staff within the team to ensure that studies are managed in line with all relevant legal and regulatory obligations and will lead the ongoing development of research quality management systems. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The post holder will set, monitor and continuously improve the research services whilst ensuring ongoing evaluation of appropriate governance and operational systems that are straight-forward for our researchers to navigate through. The post holder will provide expert sponsorship and research governance advice and support to a complex, and expanding research portfolio. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;pplicants will possess management and leadership experience within clinical research environment. Networking regionally and nationally, they will be committed to professional development, teaching and education for research staff at all levels.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Candidates must be educated to degree level, ideally with a post-graduate level qualification and substantial research governance experience. They must have excellent communication and inter-personal skills and the ability to receive and impart information accurately. They will promote and maintain high professional standards, respond proactively to changing research and regulatory requirements, whilst meeting challenging targets. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We would like all candidates to fully understand the nature of the role, enquiries are very much welcomed and can be directed to Becky Haley, Research Operations Manager on 02476 966198 or Ceri Jones,&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Head of R&amp;D on 02476 965031.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview Date: 12th November 2020 (Provisional)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameBecky HaleyJob titleR&amp;D Business Development ManagerEmail addressbecky.haley@uhcw.nhs.ukTelephone number02476 966198&lt;/p&gt;
